body_html:
@jubjamie is correct that all we have about anaconda is community supported.
If you are referring to a tutorial in www.tensorflow.org, please feel free to send a PR, as all the documentation there is in our repository.
If this is a tutorial in google developers sites, please share the link so that we can see which tutorial is causing the confusion.
If you are talking about another tutorial, we wont be able to help you with those, and you will have to reach out to the site/tutorial owners.

body:
@jubjamie is correct that all we have about anaconda is community supported.
If you are referring to a tutorial in `www.tensorflow.org`, please feel free to send a PR, as all the documentation there is in our repository.
If this is a tutorial in google developers sites, please share the link so that we can see which tutorial is causing the confusion.
If you are talking about another tutorial, we wont be able to help you with those, and you will have to reach out to the site/tutorial owners.
